article.headline: Binghamton 73, Vermont 67
article.story: VESTAL, N.Y. -- Greer Wright scored 30 points and had 10 rebounds to lead Binghamton to a 73-67 victory over Vermont on Sunday. Wright was 10-for-15 from the field and the Bearcats (8-13, 3-3 America East Conference) were 10-for-12 from the line in the final 1:33 to defeat Vermont (14-7, 5-2) for the third straight time. Mahamoud Jabbi added 14 points, 10 rebounds and four blocks for Binghamton. He was 4-for-4 from the line in the final 1:06 and had two blocks in the last 5 seconds. The Bearcats were 19-for-25 from the line in the second half after going 5-for-10 in the first half. Binghamton took a 28-20 halftime lead as Vermont shot 26.1 percent from the field (6-for-23) in the first half. Moussa Camara added 14 points for Binghamton. Maurice Joseph scored 29 points, Marqus Blakely had 14 points and 12 rebounds, and Joey Accaoui added 11 for Vermont.
